<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Cordath:
[B]Ask yourself if the kind of summoning that magicians do is the same as the sort of summoning that involves relocating someone's corpse from one end of the zone to another.  Magcian summoning involves calling forth items and beings from thin air or some other plane of existance.  Summoning a player's body is about transporting existing matter.  Same word, different meanings.  If any other class were to get a corpse teleporting spell it would be one of the classes that are already masters of teleporting existing matter.  Namely, wizards or druids.

Summon corpse fits well with the necromancer class and I'm not arguing that any other class should get this ability.  It would be nice if more than one class had it, since it would  then be easier to find someone to get your corpse, but then again, how often is your corpse going to be so lost that you have to spend 100+P on a reagent to get it back?  Not an everday occurence I'm sure!  

I find it reassuring to know that, were I summoned up by the gods themselves and pulped in some place where I have no hope of retreiving my body, there would be a way to obtain my corpse without GM intervention.  Verant probably just got tired of seeing the planes full of naked mages and tanks in expendable gear with neatly organized rows of dueled corpses laying around outside the planes.  =)[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
